text: Jørgen Frandsen (born October 31, 1944) is a former Danish handball player who competed in the 1972 Summer Olympics and in the 1976 Summer Olympics. He played his club handball with IF Stadion. In 1972, he was part of the Denmark national handball team which finished thirteenth in the 1972 Olympic tournament. He played three matches and scored one goal. Four years later, he finished eighth with the Danish team in the 1976 Olympic tournament.
